Gov survey boat, probably was going to be used for scoping out lake bottoms, says in the note at the bottom that it was involved in a road accident, but was fully repaired, and that the engines were never used

FWIW I went to the Henley Boat webpage as I noted they were the Manufacturer, they are on Manitoulin Island , very interesting, they make all manner of welded aluminum boats from 18 foot recreational/ workboats up to the size of the " Maid of the Mist  III " and ferries.
